  "theorem_claim": "Proposition (Evidence-Chain Uptake). Let IO denote material observability (what evidence the agent is given), U denote agentic uptake (the agent incorporating real data into its execution chain and avoiding synthetic substitution), and F denote reconstruction fidelity (ECRF). Then: (i) IO is necessary but not sufficient for F; (ii) U mediates IO→F; specifically floor-break (F>0.50) is achieved iff (real_data_used ∧ ¬synth), and is independent of refcode_used; (iii) synth (synthetic substitution) is a structural agentic failure mode that collapses F to the 0.50 gate regardless of IO. Corollary: code availability (IO3 ref_code_available) does not guarantee code uptake (refcode_used), and code uptake does not guarantee grounding (¬synth). Evidence: R124, n=34 DONE IO3 runs — real_data∧¬synth: 100% break (mean 0.703); synth=True: 0% break (mean 0.497); refcode_used: 25% break (3/4 still synthesized)."
